cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it together with the OFIQ reference paper and the underlying ISO standard. See docs/CITING.md."
title: "ofiq-syngen: ISO/IEC 29794-5 component-aligned synthetic face image quality degradation"
abstract: >-
  ofiq-syngen generates controlled, OFIQ-aligned synthetic face image
  degradations targeting the 28 ISO/IEC 29794-5 quality components. Each
  perturbation operates on the same image regions OFIQ measures, with
  multi-standard cross-references to ISO/IEC 19794-5 and ICAO Doc 9303
  Part 9. Designed as the canonical synthetic-degradation companion to
  the BSI OFIQ reference implementation.
authors:
  - family-names: Storey
    given-names: Aaron W.
    email: aaron@astoreyai.com
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"
    affiliation: "Clarkson University"
version: 0.5.2
date-released: "2026-05-02"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/astoreyai/ofiq-syngen"
url: "https://github.com/astoreyai/ofiq-syngen"
keywords:
  - biometrics
  - face image quality
  - OFIQ
  - ISO/IEC 29794-5
  - ISO/IEC 19794-5
  - ICAO 9303
  - synthetic degradation
  - face recognition
references:
